# Date Picker – System Standard

Use the **DatePicker** from `@ds` for all date filtering and selection. Do not create custom date pickers or use raw `DateInput` for filter bars.

## Import

```tsx
import { DatePicker } from '@ds'
```

## Usage

```tsx
<DatePicker
  dateFrom={filters.dateFrom}
  dateTo={filters.dateTo}
  onChange={(from, to) => {
    setFilter('dateFrom', from)
    setFilter('dateTo', to)
  }}
/>
```

## Props

| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `dateFrom` | `string \| null` | Start date (YYYY-MM-DD) |
| `dateTo` | `string \| null` | End date (YYYY-MM-DD). For single date, use same as dateFrom |
| `onChange` | `(from, to) => void` | Called when selection changes |
| `placeholder` | `string` | Optional placeholder when empty |
| `className` | `string` | Optional trigger button classes |
| `minWidth` | `string` | Optional min width (default: 10rem) |

## Where to Use

- Transfers filters
- Accounting / ledger filters
- Reports and dashboards
- Any page needing date range or single-date selection

## Locale

Translations live in `components.json` under `datePicker` (Today, Yesterday, Last 7 days, etc.).
